	font-style: italic;

		Contains all 'Arabic Roots' for the 'Arabic Letter'.


&encoding;

superEntry.entry:
daniIoCN dnIC dnyC dnY
daniIoCN (AZ, Lh, T, S, M, Msb, K) and daAniYN↓, (Lh, T, S, * M, K,) applied to a man, Low, ignoble, or mean, in his actions; not caring for what he does, nor for what is said to him: (S:) or bad, corrupt, or foul, in respect of the belly and the genital member [i. e. in respect of appetite for food and for sexual enjoyment]; not caring for what he does, nor for what is said to him: (AZ, Lh, T, M, K:) and [accord. to some,] i. q. xasiysN [app. as meaning contemptible]; (S, M, K;) like daniIRN, without C; (Msb;) and destitute of good: (S:) but some make a distinction between daniIoCN and daniIRN; saying that the latter means xsys; (T, Msb;) and the former, as explained by AZ and Lh; and this is the truth; (T;) or that daniIoCN means laYiymN [i. e. low, ignoble, or mean, as contr. of kariymN]: (Msb:) daniIoCN is also applied to an action: (M, K: * [see 4:]) and signifies likewise, (K,) or as some say, and so daAniYN↓, (M,) one in whom is little or no good;
contemned or contemptible, mean, paltry, or of no weight or worth: (M, K:) the pl. of daniIoCN is OadoniyaMCu, (AZ, T, M,) or OadoniYaMCu, (Lh, T, TA,) or OadonaMCN, (K, TA,) like OaXoraAfN pl. of XariyfN, (TA,) and dunaMCN, (K,) which is anomalous, (TA,) or dunaOLCu. (M.)
